The paper discusses the issue of test data reuse in machine learning workflows, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the ImageNet ILSVRC benchmark, which is a computer vision benchmark, and discusses the similarity between models proposed for this benchmark. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of large scale hyperparameter search, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also discusses the issue of overfitting, which is a common problem in the field of computer security, falling under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
